data.name: RichTextBox2.Text
data.value:
The tool measure the cost of heating a room from an intitial temperature to the desired one. The inputs from the user are the volume of the room (measured in m³), the temperature increase difference measured in (c°), the material type used for the heating (gas,electricity or wood) and the country where the material is aquired ( Germany,Italy or Sweden).
The calculate button gives the output of the energy that the heating device need to produce and the cost of the process. The energy is calculated in KJ and the cost in Cents.The RankThem button shows two tables where the results are ordered based on witch material is more convinient to use in a specific country or witch country has the cheapest material used for the heating.
